How to convert two longs to a byte array = how to convert UUID to byte array?: :I am using Javas UUID and need to convert a UUID to a byte Array. Strangely the UUID Class does not provide a "toBytes()" method.I already found out about the two methods:UUID.getMostSignificantBits()andUUID.getLeasSignificantBits()But how to get this into a byte array? the result should be a byte[] with those tow values. I somehow need to do Bitshifting but, how?update:I found: ByteBuffer byteBuffer = MappedByteBuffer.allocate(2); byteBuffer.putLong(uuid.getMostSignificantBits()); byteBuffer.putLong(uuid.getLeastSignificantBits());Is this approach corret? Are there any other methods (for learning purposes)?Thanks very much!!Jens
I think you can use the following code:
byte[] uuidBytes = new byte[16];
uuidBytes[0] = (byte) (uuid.getMostSignificantBits() >> 56);
uuidBytes[1] = (byte) (uuid.getMostSignificantBits() >> 48);
uuidBytes[2] = (byte) (uuid.getMostSignificantBits() >> 40);
uuidBytes[3] = (byte) (uuid.getMostSignificantBits() >> 32);
uuidBytes[4] = (byte) (uuid.getMostSignificantBits() >> 24);
uuidBytes[5] = (byte) (uuid.getMostSignificantBits() >> 8);
uuidBytes[6] = (byte) (uuid.getMostSignificantBits());
uuidBytes[7] = (byte) (uuid.getLeastSignificantBits() >> 56);
uuidBytes[8] = (byte) (uuid.getLeastSignificantBits() >> 48);
uuidBytes[9] = (byte) (uuid.getLeastSignificantBits() >> 40);
uuidBytes[10] = (byte) (uuid.getLeastSignificantBits() >> 32);
uuidBytes[11] = (byte) (uuid.getLeastSignificantBits() >> 24);
uuidBytes[12] = (byte) (uuid.getLeastSignificantBits() >> 8);
uuidBytes[13] = (byte) (uuid.getLeastSignificantBits());
